      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "This 997.1 Carrera is a driver-focused example featuring the 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant mated to a precise G97 6-speed manual transaxle. Mechanically sound, it has received the critical LN Engineering IMS bearing retrofit and a fresh rear main seal. The suspension retains its composure via Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM), with all bushings and ball joints showing no significant deflection. Braking performance is sharp, utilized by four-piston monoblock calipers and cross-drilled rotors with ample life remaining. The car exhibits minor cosmetic patina consistent with a well-maintained enthusiast vehicle, but the structural integrity and drivetrain synchronization remain top-tier.",
      "price": 36500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 41
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_12_listing_3",
